```sh nuts update ```
       check if a newer version of ```sh nuts``` or any of the provided <ids>
       is available in the current workspace and perform update by downloading (fetch) 
       and installing the artifact. The updated version is promoted to 'default' version.

#!include</net/thevpc/nuts/includes/standard-command.ntf>

##) SYNOPSIS:
```sh nuts update [<-options>]... <ids> ...  <args> ...```

   update the ```sh nuts``` to the latest version. If --force is armed, will re-download the artifacts and its dependencies.

```sh nuts update [ --to-version <version> ]```
   update the current workspace to latest version or to the given version if provided.

##) OPTIONS:
   ```sh -a | --all``` : force updates of both workspace's api, runtime extensions and installed artifacts
   ```sh -w | --ws | --workspace``` : update all workspace's related artifacts (api, runtime and extensions)
   ```sh -i | --installed``` : update all installed artifacts
   ```sh -e | --extensions``` : update all workspace's extensions
   ```sh -c | --companions``` : update all companions
   ```sh -r | --runtime``` : update workspace's runtime artifact (minor workspace update)
   ```sh -A | --api``` : update workspace's api (major workspace update)
   ```sh -v <version>```
   or ```sh --to-version <version>```
        : force updates to the provided <version> (may be a downgrade)
   <args> ...        : provide arguments to pass to updater

##) EXAMPLES
```sh nuts update --help```
            show this help and exit
       
```sh nuts update```
            update workspace
       
```sh nuts netbeans-launcher```
            update netbeans-launcher

